        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>You come from a long line of skilled hunters and trackers and have a particularly keen sense of smell.</p>\n<p>You gain imprecise scent with a range of 30 feet. This means you can use your sense of smell to determine a creature's location. The GM will usually double the range if you're downwind from the creature or halve the range if you're upwind.</p>\n<p>In addition, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Track]{Track} a creature or object if you've smelled it before.</p>"
